SIMPLE: royalty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Royalty
<hw>Roy"al*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Royalties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OF.
<ets>roialt⟦eacute⟧</ets>, <ets>royault⟦eacute⟧</ets>, F.
<ets>royaut⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Royal</er>, and cf.
<er>Regality</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being royal; the
condition or quality of a royal person; kingship; kingly office;
sovereignty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Royalty</qex> by birth was the sweetest way of majesty.</q>
<rj><qau>Holyday.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The person of a king or sovereign; majesty; <as>as,
in the presence of <ex>royalty</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For thus his <qex>royalty</qex> doth speak.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An emblem of royalty; -- usually in the plural,
meaning <xex>regalia</xex>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wherefore do I assume⟦br⟧
These <qex>royalties</qex>, and not refuse to reign?</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Kingliness; spirit of regal authority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In his <qex>royalty</qex> of nature⟦br⟧
Reigns that which would be fear'd.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Domain; province; sphere.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>That which is due to a sovereign, as a seigniorage
on gold and silver coined at the mint, metals taken from mines, etc.;
the tax exacted in lieu of such share; imperiality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>A share of the product or profit (as of a mine,
forest, etc.), reserved by the owner for permitting another to use the
property.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>8.</sn> <def>Hence <fld>(Com.)</fld>, a duty paid by a
manufacturer to the owner of a patent or a copyright at a certain rate
for each article manufactured; or, a percentage paid to the owner of an
article by one who hires the use of it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Royne</ent>⟦br⟧
